# Design System — Modern SaaS (Linear / Stripe / Vercel lineage)

Apply this style to every surface. Precedence when rules conflict: Accessibility → Hierarchy → Spacing → Depth → Color → Motion.

---

## 1. Core principles

1. **Minimal, not sterile.** Strip everything that doesn't serve the user's task. Then add *just enough* warmth (colored shadow, soft glow, tinted surface) so it feels alive.
2. **Hierarchy through weight, size, and color — never through borders or boxes.** If a user can't tell the primary action at a glance, the design is broken.
3. **One job per element.** A banner either announces or prompts action, not both at equal weight. A badge either counts or alerts, not both.
4. **Use accent color sparingly.** Accent is for the *one* thing you want clicked. Everything else is neutral.
5. **Respect the grid.** All spacing, sizing, and radii come from the systems below. No arbitrary numbers.
6. **Pixel-perfect always.** Prefer real `border` + real `box-shadow` over hacks. Avoid sub-pixel tricks (half-pixel borders, `background-clip` layering) — they fail at 1× zoom and in dark mode.

---

## 2. Color tokens (required)

Every project MUST define these tokens. Never hard-code colors outside the token layer.

```css
:root {
  /* Neutrals (warm paper base; swap to cool #f8f9fb for a "tech" feel) */
  --ink: #1a1613;              /* primary text */
  --paper: #f8f5f0;            /* page background */
  --warm-gray: #e8e2da;        /* borders, dividers */
  --muted: #9a918a;            /* secondary text, labels */
  --card-bg: #fffdf9;          /* raised card surface */
  --surface-raised: #ffffff;   /* chips/pills that sit ON cards or banners */

  /* Accent (one accent per product; RGB variant required for rgba()) */
  --accent: #4149d8;
  --accent-rgb: 65, 73, 216;

  /* Semantic (only if needed) */
  --status-success: #3d7a4a;
  --status-warning: #b8892e;
  --status-danger: #b35a5a;

  /* Depth tokens (derived from accent) */
  --border-soft: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.2);
  --glow-soft: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.08);
  --shadow-surface: 0 1px 2px rgba(26, 22, 19, 0.04),
                    0 6px 18px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.07);
  --shadow-highlight-top: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  --shadow-btn: 0 1px 2px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.28),
                0 2px 8px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.22);
  --shadow-btn-hover: 0 2px 4px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.32),
                      0 4px 14px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.28);
  --focus-ring: 0 0 0 3px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.22);
}

.theme-dark {
  --ink: #e4e6ee;
  --paper: #14151a;
  --warm-gray: #262830;
  --muted: #72767f;
  --card-bg: #1c1e25;
  --surface-raised: #1f2128;
  --accent: #5b63e8;           /* accent shifts lighter in dark mode */
  --accent-rgb: 91, 99, 232;
  --border-soft: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.28);
  --glow-soft: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.14);
  --shadow-surface: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4),
                    0 8px 24px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.14);
  --shadow-highlight-top: inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
  --shadow-btn: 0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.35),
                0 2px 10px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.35);
  --shadow-btn-hover: 0 2px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4),
                      0 6px 18px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.45);
  --focus-ring: 0 0 0 3px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.35);
}
```

### Contrast requirements (WCAG)

- Primary text (`--ink` on `--paper`): must be ≥ 7:1 (AAA).
- Primary button label (white on `--accent`): must be ≥ 4.5:1 (AA), aim for ≥ 7:1.
- Muted text (`--muted`): must be ≥ 4.5:1 against its background.
- Focus ring must be visible on every interactive element.

---

## 3. Spacing — 4/8px grid (strict)

Only these values: `4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48, 64, 80, 96`.

| Use case | Value |
|---|---|
| Icon-to-text gap | `8px` |
| Inline element gap (within a row) | `8–12px` |
| Button internal padding (vertical / horizontal) | `9px / 16px` (height 34px) |
| Card padding | `20–24px` |
| Banner padding | `16px 20px` |
| Section vertical rhythm | `24–32px` |
| Page gutter | `32–48px` |
| Major section separation | `48–64px` |

**Never use** `3px, 5px, 7px, 10px, 14px, 18px, 22px`. If you're tempted, you're off-grid.

---

## 4. Radii system (monotonic)

Radii get **smaller** as elements nest deeper. Never mix pill-shapes with rounded-rectangles on the same surface.

| Element | Radius |
|---|---|
| Page-level container / modal | `16px` |
| Card, banner, panel | `12px` |
| Button, input, icon-container, chip | `8px` |
| Small tag, inline dot | `6px` or `999px` (only for count pills) |
| Circle (avatars, not icons) | `50%` |

**Forbidden:** `10px`, `14px`, `20px` radii. Pill-shape (`999px`) only for count badges and status tags, never for buttons.

---

## 5. Typography

```css
--font-body: 'Inter', 'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
--font-serif: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif; /* optional, for editorial headings */
```

| Role | Size / weight / tracking |
|---|---|
| Display H1 | 32–40px / 300–400 (thin) / -0.02em |
| Section heading H2 | 20–24px / 500 / -0.01em |
| Card/banner title | 14–15px / 600 / -0.006em |
| Body | 14–15px / 400 / 0 |
| Secondary text | 13px / 400 / 0, color `--muted` |
| Label / caps | 10–11px / 500 / +1.5em, uppercase, color `--muted` |
| Button | 13px / 600 / -0.005em |
| Count badge | 11px / 600 / 0, `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums` |

Line-height: body `1.5`, headings `1.2`, buttons `1`, single-line labels `1`.

---

## 6. Depth — shadows & glows

### The two-layer shadow (signature move)

Every raised surface (card, banner, menu, modal) uses **two shadow layers**:

```css
box-shadow:
  0 1px 2px rgba(26, 22, 19, 0.04),           /* tight contact */
  0 6px 18px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.07),   /* soft colored lift */
  inset 0 1px 0 rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);     /* top highlight */
```

Why: a single gray shadow looks like a cardboard cutout. The *colored* second layer makes the surface feel "lit" by the accent. The inset highlight mimics real edge-light.

### The corner glow (Linear move)

Optional atmosphere on hero surfaces and banners. A heavily-blurred radial gradient anchored in one corner:

```css
.surface { position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
.surface::before {
  content: '';
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  background: radial-gradient(
    120% 180% at 0% 0%,
    var(--glow-soft) 0%,
    transparent 55%
  );
  pointer-events: none;
}
.surface > * { position: relative; } /* keep children above the glow */
```

### Button shadow

Filled primary buttons use `--shadow-btn` — saturated accent tint so the button looks lit from its own color.

### Rules

- Never use pure black shadows in light mode; use `rgba(ink, 0.04–0.08)` or tinted accent.
- Never stack more than 3 shadow layers.
- No drop-shadow on flat elements like labels, inputs at rest, or dividers.

---

## 7. Components

### Button

Three variants. Height `34px`, radius `8px`, font 13px/600.

```html
<button class="btn btn-primary">Primary</button>
<button class="btn btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
<button class="btn btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
```

```css
.btn {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  height: 34px; padding: 0 16px; gap: 8px;
  border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid transparent;
  font: 600 13px/1 var(--font-body);
  letter-spacing: -0.005em;
  cursor: pointer; white-space: nowrap;
  transition: box-shadow .18s ease, transform .18s ease,
              background .18s ease, border-color .18s ease, color .18s ease;
}
.btn:focus-visible { outline: none; box-shadow: var(--focus-ring); }
.btn:active { transform: translateY(0); }

.btn-primary {
  background: var(--accent); color: #fff;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn);
}
.btn-primary:hover { box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn-hover); transform: translateY(-1px); }
.btn-primary:focus-visible { box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn), var(--focus-ring); }

.btn-secondary {
  background: transparent; color: var(--muted);
  border-color: var(--warm-gray);
}
.btn-secondary:hover {
  background: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.06);
  border-color: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.3);
  color: var(--ink); transform: translateY(-1px);
}

.btn-ghost { background: transparent; color: var(--muted); }
.btn-ghost:hover { background: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.06); color: var(--ink); }
```

**Rules:**
- **One primary per screen-region.** Two filled buttons side-by-side = broken hierarchy. If you need two actions, secondary must be ghost.
- Never use `min-width` on buttons. Size to label + padding.
- Never pill-shape a button (`border-radius: 999px`). That's for tags/badges.
- Icon-only buttons: 34×34px, 8px radius, 18px icon.

### Card

```css
.card {
  background: var(--card-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 20px 24px;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-surface), var(--shadow-highlight-top);
  transition: border-color .2s, box-shadow .2s, transform .2s;
}
.card:hover {
  border-color: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.3);
  transform: translateY(-1px);
}
```

### Banner / notification

**Banners are tiered by urgency × frequency, NOT by "banners all get the hero treatment."** The more often a banner appears, the quieter it must be. Pick the tier *before* writing CSS.

| Tier | When to use | Treatment |
|---|---|---|
| **T1 — Routine** (default) | Recurring housekeeping advisories the user sees every session ("5 stale tabs", "3 duplicates found", "2 items saved for later") | Neutral — looks like a sibling of cards |
| **T2 — Action required** | Occasional, user must respond but not critical ("re-auth needed", "quota at 80%") | Tinted — accent border + soft-accent shadow, keep inset highlight, **no corner glow** |
| **T3 — Critical / one-time** | Rare, high-stakes ("payment failed", "sync error", "destructive confirm") | Full kit — tinted fill + border + corner glow + inset highlight + two-layer colored shadow. Usually paired with `role="alert"`. |

**Default to T1.** Escalate only with evidence (threshold count, severity class, explicit criticality). A banner you see every day is T1 no matter how "important" it feels.

```css
/* T1 — Routine (the default). Sits alongside cards, not above them. */
.banner {
  position: relative;
  background: var(--paper);
  border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray);
  border-radius: 12px;
  padding: 16px 20px;
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-surface);
  /* No ::before glow. No inset highlight. Color lives in the CTA, not the shell. */
}

/* T2 — Action required. Add this class OR gate via threshold. */
.banner.is-action {
  background: var(--paper);
  border-color: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.22);
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-surface), var(--shadow-highlight-top);
}

/* T3 — Critical. Full glow treatment. */
.banner.is-critical {
  background: linear-gradient(180deg,
    rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.06),
    rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.02));
  border-color: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.28);
  box-shadow:
    0 1px 2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04),
    0 6px 18px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.1),
    inset 0 1px 0 var(--banner-highlight);
  overflow: hidden;
}
.banner.is-critical::before { /* corner glow */
  content: '';
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  background: radial-gradient(60% 80% at 0% 0%,
    rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.12), transparent 60%);
  pointer-events: none;
}
.banner.is-critical > * { position: relative; }
```

**The color-as-signal rule (new & enforced):**
Inside any banner, count the amber-saturated elements. If you find more than **two** (typically: the count badge + the primary CTA), you have color noise. Everything else — background, border, icon container, title, secondary buttons — should be neutral. Same applies to sage, rose, etc. Accent saturation is a spotlight; a spotlight on everything lights nothing.

Add `role="status"` + `aria-live="polite"` for T1/T2 banners, `role="alert"` + `aria-live="assertive"` for T3.

### Chip / pill / tag

For listing items (tabs, users, file references):

```css
.chip {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
  background: var(--surface-raised);
  border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray);
  border-radius: 8px;
  padding: 6px 10px;
  font: 500 12px/1 var(--font-body);
  color: var(--ink);
  transition: border-color .15s, box-shadow .15s;
}
.chip:hover {
  border-color: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.35);
  box-shadow: 0 1px 2px rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.1);
}
```

**Rule:** When chips sit on a *tinted* surface (like a banner), their background MUST be `--surface-raised`, not the same tint. Same-family tints flatten into soup (violates Gestalt figure/ground).

### Count badge

```css
.count-badge {
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  min-width: 22px; height: 20px; padding: 0 7px;
  border-radius: 999px;
  background: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.1);
  color: var(--accent);
  font: 600 11px/1 var(--font-body);
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
}
```

**Rule:** Count badges are *neutral*, not alarming. Never use solid accent fill + white text for counts — that's an alert pattern and will fight the primary CTA for attention.

### Input

```css
.input {
  height: 36px; padding: 0 12px;
  background: var(--card-bg);
  border: 1px solid var(--warm-gray);
  border-radius: 8px;
  font: 400 14px/1 var(--font-body);
  color: var(--ink);
  transition: border-color .15s, box-shadow .15s;
}
.input::placeholder { color: var(--muted); }
.input:focus {
  outline: none;
  border-color: var(--accent);
  box-shadow: var(--focus-ring);
}
```

### Icon container (product-icon style)

For icons inside banners, list rows, or cards:

```css
.icon-wrap {
  width: 28px; height: 28px;
  border-radius: 8px;
  background: rgba(var(--accent-rgb), 0.12);
  display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
}
.icon-wrap svg {
  width: 16px; height: 16px;
  color: var(--accent); stroke-width: 2;
}
```

Sizes: `24px` (inline), `28px` (default), `40px` (hero).
**Never use `border-radius: 50%` for non-avatar icons.**

